    <div class="document-title">LETTER OF DEMAND TO MECHANIC</div>
    <div class="document-subtitle">For: Will</div>
    <div class="document-date">Date: 12 April 2025</div>
    
    <p class="document-paragraph">[Your Name: Will]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Your Address]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[City, State, Postcode]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Phone: ]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Email: wia@asd.com]  </p><p class="document-signature">[Date: 2023-10-15]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Business Name: asd]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Business Address]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">Dear [Mechanic&#039;s Name or Business Manager],</p><p class="document-bullet">**Re: Letter of Demand for Vehicle Damage During Servicing**</p><p class="document-paragraph">I am writing to formally demand compensation for damage that occurred to my vehicle while it was in your care for servicing on 20th September 9999. This letter serves as a formal notice under the Australian Consumer Law (ACL), which mandates that services must be provided with due care and skill.</p><p class="document-bullet">**Timeline of Events:**</p><p class="document-paragraph">1. **Vehicle Drop-off:** My vehicle was delivered to your premises on 20th September 9999 for servicing.</p><p class="document-paragraph">2. **Damage Discovery:** Upon retrieval of my vehicle, I discovered the following damage: asdasdasdasdasd.</p><p class="document-paragraph">Under the ACL, service providers are required to perform services with due care and skill, taking all necessary precautions to avoid damage to the consumer&#039;s property. It is evident that this obligation has not been met, resulting in damage to my vehicle. </p><p class="document-bullet">**Consumer Rights Under Australian Consumer Law:**</p><p class="document-paragraph">The ACL stipulates that services must be rendered with due care and skill (Section 60), and a failure to do so constitutes a breach of consumer guarantees. By damaging my vehicle, your business has failed to uphold this guarantee, and I am entitled to seek remedies for this breach.</p><p class="document-bullet">**Demand for Remedy:**</p><p class="document-paragraph">I am seeking full compensation for the repair costs associated with the damage to my vehicle. As of this date, I have not obtained an independent quote nor filed an insurance claim, but the expectation is for your business to cover the full cost of repairs.</p><p class="document-signature">Please note that I am not willing to sign any release of future claims or non-disparagement agreement as part of the resolution process.</p><p class="document-bullet">**Deadline for Response:**</p><p class="document-signature">I require a written response within 7 days of the date of this letter, confirming your agreement to cover the repair costs. Failure to respond satisfactorily by [Date: 2023-10-22] will result in my escalating this matter to Consumer Affairs Victoria and, if necessary, pursuing the matter through the Victorian Civil and Administrative Tribunal (VCAT).</p><p class="document-paragraph">I trust this matter can be resolved amicably and promptly. Please contact me directly at [Phone: ] or [Email: wia@asd.com] to discuss the necessary arrangements for compensation.</p><p class="document-paragraph">Yours sincerely,</p><p class="document-signature">[Signature]</p><p class="document-paragraph">Will  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Your Name]  </p><p class="document-bullet">---</p><p class="document-paragraph">Please ensure all placeholders such as addresses, dates, and names are filled with the appropriate information before sending this letter.</p>
    
